1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,090
Summary To be a more effective leader, put these four leadership principles to work.

2
00:00:07,090 --> 00:00:08,851
1.

3
00:00:09,281 --> 00:00:12,610
Trade minds with the people you want to influence.

4
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:18,210
It's easy to get others to do what you want them to do if you'll see things through their eyes.

5
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:21,650
Ask yourself this question before you act.

6
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:26,690
What would I think of this if I exchanged places with the other person?

7
00:00:27,761 --> 00:00:32,371
Two, apply the Be Human rule in your dealings with others.

8
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:35,570
Ask, what is the human way to handle this?

9
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:39,891
In everything you do, show that you put other people first.

10
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:43,891
Just give other people the kind of treatment you like to receive.

11
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,491
You'll be rewarded.

12
00:00:46,721 --> 00:00:51,570
Three, think progress, believe in progress, push for progress.

13
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:54,451
Think improvement in everything you do.

14
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:57,251
Think high standards in everything you do.

15
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:03,011
Over a period of time, subordinates tend to become carbon copies of their chief.

16
00:01:03,281 --> 00:01:06,531
Be sure the master copy is worth duplicating.

17
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,090
Make this a personal resolution.

18
00:01:09,201 --> 00:01:15,011
At home, at work, in community life, if it's progress, I'm for it.

19
00:01:15,281 --> 00:01:16,851
4.

20
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:22,130
Take time out to confer with yourself and tap your supreme thinking power.

21
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,931
Managed solitude pays off.

22
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,650
Use it to release your creative power.

23
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:31,650
Use it to find solutions to personal and business problems.

24
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:35,811
So, spend some time alone every day just for thinking.

25
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:39,491
Use the thinking technique all great leaders use.

26
00:01:39,681 --> 00:01:41,570
Confer with yourself.

27
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:53,491
How to Use the Magic of Thinking Big in Life's Most Crucial Situations There is magic in thinking big,

28
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,731
but it is so easy to forget.

29
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:01,251
When you hit some rough spots, there is danger that your thinking will shrink in size,

30
00:02:01,281 --> 00:02:03,650
and when it does, you lose.

31
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:09,971
Here are some brief guides for staying big when you're tempted to use the small approach.

32
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:15,891
Perhaps you'll want to put these guides on small cards for even handier reference.

33
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,491
A.

34
00:02:17,681 --> 00:02:22,130
When little people try to drive you down, think big.

35
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:29,411
To be sure, there are some people who want you to lose, to experience misfortune, to be reprimanded.

36
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:33,331
But these people can't hurt you if you'll remember three things.

37
00:02:33,681 --> 00:02:37,891
One, you win when you refuse to fight petty people.

38
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:41,251
Fighting little people reduces you to their size.

39
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,610
Stay big.

40
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,570
Two, expect to be sniped at.

41
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,411
It's proof you're growing.

42
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:52,371
Three, remind yourself that snipers are psychologically sick.

43
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,491
Be big.

44
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,251
Feel sorry for them.

45
00:02:56,400 --> 00:03:00,931
Think big enough to be immune to the attacks of petty people.

46
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:08,371
B, when that I haven't got what it takes feeling creeps up on you, think big.

47
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:12,210
Remember, if you think you are weak, you are.

48
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,011
If you think you're inadequate, you are.

49
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:18,130
If you think you're second class, you are.

50
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:23,731
Whip that natural tendency to sell yourself short with these tools.

51
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,491
1.

52
00:03:25,681 --> 00:03:26,851
Look important.

53
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,851
It helps you think important.

54
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:34,291
How you look on the outside has a lot to do with how you feel on the inside.

55
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,130
2.

56
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,451
Concentrate on your assets.

57
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:42,770
Build a sell-yourself-to-yourself commercial and use it.

58
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,251
Learn to supercharge yourself.

59
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,491
Know your positive self.

60
00:03:47,491 --> 00:03:49,491
3.

61
00:03:49,761 --> 00:03:52,371
Put other people in proper perspective.

62
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:57,251
The other person is just another human being, so why be afraid of him?

63
00:03:58,241 --> 00:04:02,050
Think big enough to see how good you really are.

64
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:09,281
C. When an argument or quarrel seems inevitable, think big.
